OL,3,CAsian family 'targeted' in Hartlepool
OL,4,Cdisorder will now leave the town
OL,6,FHe said he was with his mother at the
OL,7,Ftime of the incident during which she
OL,8,Fhad a panic attack.
OL,10,FWhen asked if he was scared, he said:
OL,11,F"I was more worried about my mum."
OL,13,FHe said they have lived in the
OL,14,Fproperty for two years and that he
OL,15,F"recognised faces" of those inside of
OL,16,Fhis house.
OL,18,FThe man is now planning to leave
OL,19,FHartlepool for good and in a bid to
OL,20,Ffind somewhere he believes is safe for
OL,21,Fhis mother.
